  "text": "Acute viral respiratory infection. Although Ms. J does have an acute respiratory viral infection that needs to be treated, the manifestations of HF are the cause of most of her symptoms and findings. And although her prior oncologic therapies have likely contributed to the condition of HF, the acute failure she is experiencing has been triggered by infection. In comparison with other precipitating morbidities such as atrial fibrillation, HF precipitated by infection is associated with a worse outcome [CITATION_1] , and thus needs to be managed quickly and aggressively.",
